first experiences with technology is being deprived of it for most of her early life. This lead to becoming &#8220;that&#8221; friend who &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2014/10/14/wds-welcomes-jaimie-olmstead/">Continue reading </a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Melissa Hoppe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2255:"<p><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Jaimie.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-8591" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Jaimie-224x300.jpg" alt="Jaimie" width="224" height="300" /></a>WDS is proud to announce our newest Project Manager, <a title="Jaimie Olmstead" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/jaimie-olmstead/">Jaimie Olmstead</a>!</p>\n<p>The earliest memory Jaimie has of her first experiences with technology is being deprived of it for most of her early life. This lead to becoming &#8220;that&#8221; friend who wouldn&#8217;t want to watch movies, go outside, and do normal things friends would do during sleepovers. No. She was there to use your Super NES, swoon to the sound of a dial up modem, and play Myst until you physically had to kick her out. Shortly after, her parents would understand they could no longer subject others to this and the first computer was put into her house. Soon, Jaimie was learning HTML at 12 because everyone needs to be able to see fireworks when clicking their mouse. It was a different time, okay?</p>\n<p>Jaimie has just recently joined the WDS team as a Project Manager. With almost a decade of management experience, she&#8217;s excited to make the move to WDS, meet new clients, and help lead their team to success. She has a proven track record of client satisfaction, high standards, and consistency. Eager to learn from her creative team, Jaimie looks forward to learning the ins and outs of WordPress so she&#8217;s able to use a well-rounded approach with every project.</p>\n<p>In Jaimie&#8217;s free time she enjoys making road trips solely centered around flea markets and antique fairs, and is constantly plagued by the notion she might have a vintage furniture hording problem. Jaimie also runs an online vintage clothing store fueled by her ruthless pillaging of every goodwill, second hand store, and estate sale she&#8217;s near. She&#8217;s also recently taken up collecting oddities. Her most prized possession is her authentic ram skull.</p>\n<p>We are very excited to have Jaimie joining our team! You can <a href="https://twitter.com/jaimieolmstead">follow her on Twitter</a> for the latest updates on her thrift shopping.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/10/14/wds-welcomes-jaimie-olmstead/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:69:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:63:"WordPress – Up and Running with Grunt, Sass, Bourbon and Neat";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:94:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/10/09